description: Get a list of lifecycle policies in your Amazon Web Services account.

parameters.name: filters
parameters.description: Streamline results based on one of the following values: Name, Status. (dict) --- A filter name and value pair that is used to return a more specific list of results from a list operation. Filters can be used to match a set of resources by specific criteria, such as tags, attributes, or IDs. name (string) --- The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive. values (list) --- The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive. (string) ---

nested_params.name: name
nested_params.description: The name of the filter. Filter names are case-sensitive.

nested_params.name: values
nested_params.description: The filter values. Filter values are case-sensitive.

nested_items.name: lifecyclePolicySummaryList
nested_items.description: A list of lifecycle policies in your Amazon Web Services account that meet the criteria specified in the request.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the lifecycle policy summary resource.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the lifecycle policy.

nested_items.name: description
nested_items.description: Optional description for the lifecycle policy.

nested_items.name: executionRole
nested_items.description: The name or Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role that Image Builder uses to run the lifecycle policy.

nested_items.name: resourceType
nested_items.description: The type of resources the lifecycle policy targets.

nested_items.name: dateCreated
nested_items.description: The timestamp when Image Builder created the lifecycle policy resource.

nested_items.name: dateUpdated
nested_items.description: The timestamp when Image Builder updated the lifecycle policy resource.

nested_items.name: dateLastRun
nested_items.description: The timestamp for the last time Image Builder ran the lifecycle policy.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The next token used for paginated responses. When this field isn't empty, there are additional elements that the service hasn't included in this request. Use this token with the next request to retrieve additional objects.
